Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @green beans{80}, then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}, adding the beans for the last ~{5%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Leave to the side until ready to use.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the garlic and @Chinese five spice{2} into the pork and cook for ~{1%min}.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{150} in a sieve.

Add the sweetcorn, cooked green beans and rice to the pork. Mix well to combine.

Stir the @ketjap manis{50}, @soy sauce{15}, @honey{15} and @water{50} for the sauce into the fried rice.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Share the pork fried rice between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts.

Scatter with the spring onion to finish. Enjoy!